<br>
Right, Everquest is the big money maker compared to such also-rans as Diablo II and the Sims.<br>
<br>
Everquest is a blip in comparison to the big games out there. It's got an economic model (that it didn't initially develop, remember) that is one that makes corporate accountants sit up and get thoughtful, but it's hardly the great trailblazer, nor is it the big economic success story you're painting it as.<br>
<br>
Everquest is the most successful Western MMORPG <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>so far</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. I have no doubt that within five years, we'll see something that will make us all forget EQ. If Sony is lucky, it's EQ2 or EQ3. But the serious competition is lining up, and it's entirely possible that EQ1 will be the high point of the EQ empire. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1587<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/03 12:54:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26138.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/phpBB2/images/avatars/gallery/Warcraft%20III/3lich.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where have all the gnomes gone?</span><hr size=1> I just hope WoW will put an end to SOEs monopole about the whole genre <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
